Dr. Issa Abu-Dayyeh
Amman, Jordan3,086 contributions
8
Lovely design
Nov 2019 • Friends
Loved it. It is a world-Fanous bridge. Now I have to admit I imagined it to be an abandoned bridge ontop of a mountain where you can meditate, if that is how you imagine it from the pictures you are up for a disappointment.

To get there, you need to go to Ba Na hills, buy a ticket for the cable car and get up to French village. There, transfer into a second cable car (Louvre station) that will take you right to the bridge.
The bridge is full of tourists walking around and taking picture, so accept this fact and appreciate its beauty lying in between the mist.
Cross it and visit the lovely botanical gardens.
Good luck!
If you find this review helpful, please press like to encourage me to post more.
